metadata.name: Modificador de eventos #70
metadata.description:
Inspired by order and entropy cellular. 

Events that modify our trajectory often go unnoticed in our time. these events that arise in the course of our lives alter the trajectory and purpose of our lives, these events are beyond our control, beyond expectations and standards. The results of these trajectories are individually unique, the experiences of what has already been covered and the curiosity of what will be found, is what moves this perpetual autonomous game in its random trajectory. The overall behavior of the system is determined by the set of rules and modular functions.

I recommend running perpetual animation and resolution adaptive livecode in fullscream mode and using headphones, click anywhere on the running animation to listen.

livecode performed in hydra.ojack.xyz
ambient music recorded in vcvrack

- press 's' to save a frame from livecode tragectory

metadata.name: VOODOOZ #278
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci‚Äôs VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

‚Ä¢ The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis‚Äô genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: Glossolalia #6
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse‚Ä¶ which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it‚Äôs about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It‚Äôs less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append ‚Äú&density=2‚Äù to the url to double the size, ‚Äú&density=3‚Äù to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append ‚Äú&grain=##‚Äù to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.

metadata.name: Step by Step #42
metadata.description:
Step by Step explores the feeling of being stuck, confined - walking the path ahead of you often only seeing the immediate next step until exhaustion. We all feel this way from time to time ‚Äî in our lives, jobs, bodies, situations ‚Äî yet in our search for something, we shouldn't forget that there can still be beauty along the path.

The project takes some inspiration from Henri Matisse, both in the aesthetics of his later works (i.e. the "Cut Outs") and metaphorically in the sense that he had underwent medical treatment which left him wheelchair- or bed-bound towards the later part of his life, forcing him to give up painting, yet in his exploration of this new creative medium which involved cutting paper and pinning them up, his unorthodox work went on to become the most transformative of his career.

Released as part of the 4th edition of the Cure¬≥ Parkinson's cure fundraiser exhibition organized by Artwise Curators and Bonhams as part of a specially comissioned selection of generative artists minting NFTs, curated by Foteini Valeonti and Alex Estorick with the support of fx(hash) at Bonhams, London from 13-17th January 2023.

---
33% of primary sales and 3% of secondary sales will be donated on-chain to Cure Parkinson‚Äôs
---

metadata.name: Verdant Brut #203
metadata.description:
Verdant translates to ‚Äúlush, green‚Äù and Brut means ‚Äúdry, raw, or unrefined.‚Äù

This series is less about impressions of nature, or vegetal growth‚Ä¶ but rather the vibrant, lush world that abstract art can provide and while certain iterations may serve Brutalist aesthetics, it tries to focus on the unrefined/raw aspect of the definition with more fluid shapes that feel irregular and organic in a playful, almost adolescent way.

Palettes inspired by MOMO, Melissa Wiederrecht, Erik Swahn, Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, Paul Klee, Mareva Millarc, Ernst Mether-BorgstroÃàm, Douglas Herbert Courtenay Auburn, Jim Harris, Alayne Spafford, Man Ray, Lajos Kassak and William Lachance. While the palettes may not always reflect their trademark colors (if they even have any) they are an homage to individual pieces by the respective artists that have influenced this series in their own way.

4878 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries.

For more info on the chosen palettes and other inspirations, see article linked from the main project page: Regarding Verdant Brut

In live mode:
‚ÄòS‚Äô : save as png (2376‚Ää√ó‚Ää3360)
‚ÄôV‚Äô : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‚Äòg=n‚Äô : no grain
‚Äòg=p‚Äô : paper grain
‚Äòh=t‚Äô : high resolution mode, 5940‚Ää√ó‚Ää8400 (Chrome only)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append ‚Äú&g=p&h=t‚Äù to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save the png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Territory B #39
metadata.description:
Territory B leaves no space unused.

---

This is a long-form series by Louis-Andr√© Labadie. Territory B is about maximalist use of space ‚Äì whether it ends up being efficient sharing or outsized greed.

It's inspired by societal artifacts like ad-laden web pages, British land division, disk space tools, and wild posting.

---

It's got features! On your keyboard:

B or M ‚Äì Toggle mono (B&W) mode.
S ‚Äì Slowed down drawing mode.
‚Üê and ‚Üí ‚Äì Adjust the drawing speed when slowed down.
V - Toggle vector preview.
D - Download as a plottable SVG file (this will respect full color vs mono mode).
K or Space ‚Äì Kiosk mode (iterates to a new composition every X seconds).
‚Üë and ‚Üì ‚Äì Adjust the kiosk mode delay.
C ‚Äì Manually cycle one iteration.

metadata.name: Waxing Crescent #78
metadata.description:
A generator for the mascot of darkness.

The moons are generated with a real-time GAN of 1.6M parameters that has been trained on thousands of photos collected on the internet.

Each grid performs a unique cycle of 29.53 days, in sync with the iconic celestial body.

Press "r" to render the full cycle as a 2s GIF.

metadata.name: Sedimentary Dissolution #452
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by the geological processes related to sedimentary dissolution. Dissolution is a form of weathering which contributes to the creation of new rocks. In this piece, various algorithms take on the role of dissolution, producing visual recombinations of the original "sedimentary rock".

Instructions ::

p : save a hi-res image
e : toggle erosion on and off
s : toggle structure on and off
a : toggle all effects on and off

If offset, rgb dissolution or cross-bedding is true you can toggle it on and off.
If these features are false pressing the key will have no effect.

o : toggle offset on and off
r : toggle rgb dissolution on and off
c : toggle cross-bedding on and off

There are 20 versions you can explore, all using the same features.
Use the left and right arrow to change the random seed. 
Pressing space will re-instantiate the original random seed.
